#What the OS actually needs

When a TCP packet arrives, it contains:

destination IP + destination port

So routing table contains things like:

default gateway
network interfaces (eth0, wlan0)
next hop router



B) Socket lookup table (VERY IMPORTANT for ft_irc)

This is what you were actually asking about.

When a packet arrives, kernel asks:

“Which process/socket should receive this?”

So it checks:

(local IP, local port) → socket fd

Example:

0.0.0.0:6667 → fd 3 (your IRC server)

👉 This is for incoming traffic